<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-07T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-07T01:00:00-05:00" n="549" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/6516: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-07T13:00:00+07:00">May 7, 1942—1
                                p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received May 7—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>523. Department’s 354, May 4, 8 p.m. The stocks in reference were not shipped
                        to place of safety and there is no likelihood of saving any portion thereof.
                        Will report further information when available.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>